shared_text:
Kamiah High School
July 30 at 1:38 PM ·

Kamiah School District registration days and times announced.

Kamiah High School:

Seniors and their parents will begin the process on Tuesday August 18th from 8:00-11 followed by the Juniors from noon-3:00 in the high school library. Wednesday August 19th Sophomores will register from 8:00-11 and Freshman from noon-3:00 in the same location. New student registration will be held August 20th from 8:00-3:00 in the high school office regardless of grade level. If you are unable to make it on registration day, please call the school secretary or the school counselor at 208-935-4067 to make other arrangements.

Tuesday, August 18th
Seniors 8am – 11 am
Juniors noon- 3:00pm

Wednesday, August 19th
Sophomores 8 – 11 am
Freshmen noon- 3:00pm

*In accordance with COVID social distancing safety protocol, we will be allowing students into the library on a staggered basis. Please allow yourself extra time should you have to wait in line.*

April 13, 20Kamiah is the small high school that offers big opportunities for students who seek to jump-start their post-secondary education by taking dual credit classes in high school. Principal Peggy Flerchinger said to think of Kamiah as “the little school that could.” Dual credit classes are those that concurrently earn high school and college credits. The program was created by the Idaho Legislature in 1997 to provide Idaho students an opportunity to earn college credits at a low cost. [ 759 more words ]

Hi I am Chloe Hescock and I am a senior at Kamiah high school and oh boy where do I begin. I played sports for 3 years of high school because at the end of my junior year I moved away. I have done 4 years of HOSA going to nationals three years in a row but due to covid 19 I was not able to compete in my fourth year of HOSA. I was class president two years in a row my sophomore and my junior year and that was an experience. I would not trade my class in for anything, they are my best friends, even though we fight the majority of the time I will miss them dearly. I want to thank everyone for always pushing me to do better and to go on to better things. Come next fall I will be attending Lewis Clark State College for pre-nursing. So here’s to the class of 2020 for the year that was kind of crazy but hey our whole class is crazy and we are going to go on to do more crazy and fun adventures so here’s to the future and here’s to you class of 2020

Chloe Hescock 👩‍🎓

post_text:
🎓Senior Showcase🎓

You never know how much something you think is menial really matters until you lose it, well that was school for me. I would end up thinking, man I hate that I have to come here everyday, but by each weekend, though I never admitted it, I missed being there especially for classes like English, Financial Algebra, and US. History. I don't know how many of my senior classmates feel the same but I'd bet ten to one it's more than they would admit. There are so many people from the school that deserve thanks, not only from me but from everyone, more than I can name here. Thank you to Mr. Mercer, Mrs. Flerchinger, who was not only our advisor but was also a friend to most of us; Mr. Martin who really deserves to be teacher of a lifetime; and last but not least Mrs. Wilcox, who went above and beyond in her job for us. Without all of you I'd have never made it this far.

"Well that happened..." Excerpt from Adam Fowler's senior quote.

Adam Fowler👨‍🎓

My name is Jordan Hrabak and I have been going to school at KHS since junior year but playing sports for KHS since freshman year. I love playing baseball and football in front of our amazing kub fans. Wasn’t apart of any clubs. I was always told high school flys by and for awhile it didn’t seem true until last year when it finally came in to realization that Graduation is right around the corner. This year especially flew by in the drop of a hat, and now with the situation we are in today it is unbelievable that we may have had our technically last day of school already. I want to thank my teachers, family and my amazing friends that helped make me who I am today and help push me to my best as well and thank all the sports coaches I have had throughout the years. After High school I am attending LCSC in the fall for automotive mechanics just to have a degree under my belt and become a police officer and then way later down the road open up a shop to work on cars. Thanks for the memories Kamiah High School. GO KUBS!

Jordan Hrabak👨‍🎓

🎓Senior Showcase🎓

My name is Sarah Bytheway. I am a sibling of 16 children and momentarily taking care of 12 of them. I was a homeschooler up until 9th grade, when I enrolled into Kamiah High School. Throughout the next four years I have participated in 4-H, basketball, theater, several different dance classes, chess tournaments, MMA, school planning and funding and many other community service functions. With the circumstances going on today, I am just grateful to be graduating and starting my new life. In which I start creating this fall at LCSC, where I plan to study Dental Hygiene. Everyone talks about high school flying by quickly and they’re right! But, don’t waste your time thinking about what you could have been during those four years. You are already starting something new each day you wake up, so enjoy that day and make it the best you can.

Sarah Bytheway👩‍🎓

post_text:
🎓Senior Showcase!🎓

I’m so proud of the class of 2020! I’m thankful for each and every one of them. Growing up with my classmates was a beautiful adventure. Now we each have evolved into courageous young adults with different lifestyles, personalities, cultures, and many more differences that distinguish us from one another. Our small town school gave us the opportunity to socialize and create friendships that could last a lifetime. School gave us each common memories that we can now reminisce over, or completely ignore! We bonded during field trips, assemblies, games, plays, and everyday class. Although I was a wallflower, and wasn’t involved in much, I didn’t miss out on the beautiful high school experience, and I thank each and every person who helped shape who I am today and helped me graduate from Kamiah High School. Sending good luck and good thoughts to all the graduates.

Katy Bashaw👩‍🎓

Kamiah School District will be taking part in the statewide "Be the Light" event. This is an event to honor the senior class of 2020, families, coaches, and spring sport athletes. This Friday, April 10th at 8:20pm the Bob Squires Complex field lights will be turned on. The lights are a beacon to show that the KSD staff along with the Kamiah community are thinking of the 2020 seniors. We know that this a painful time for them and their families. The lights will also remind us that soon we will be back together and stronger than ever! Community members are welcome to drive by the field in your cars and take pictures. Use the hashtag #BeTheLightID when you post them!

#KubTuff #KamiahStrong

Staff will continue to provide on-line and paper-and-pencil educational material, and the district will continue with breakfast and lunch delivery through May 29th. With our Board’s decision, the District will now begin the process of making final plans for student promotion, graduation, and preparation for starting the new school year next fall. post_text: Per Mr. Steve Higgins
shared_text:
Kamiah Matters
March 24 at 8:30 PM ·

Per Steve Higgins
Press Release: 3/26/20

Following directives from the State Board of Education, Kamiah School District will continue to operate with the soft closure until April 20, 2020. Teachers will continue to provide learning packets and/or on-line lessons through home delivery or in school pickup. Staff will establish timelines for due dates for the homework to be completed and returned. Students are expected to meet all timelines and will be held accountable for assigned work that can be returned to the school in person or sent back via school bus. Third quarter grades will be rolled into a second semester grade. The District will record a final semester grade at the end of the school year that totals all work for that time period.

In a continued effort to meet the needs of our community, emergency feeding will continue through April 16 and will include spring break. Food service will not be providing breakfast and lunches on Fridays.

Up to date information will be communicated as the situation changes for the District. Thank you for your patience and understanding!

The IHSAA has informed all member schools that sanctioned sports and activities for all of its member schools will be suspended effective Tuesday March 17 through April 5th.

post_text: A significant source of funding for student instruction is a local property tax called the Supplemental Levy. On Tuesday, 10 March, the ballot question asked district residents to approve funding for our schools. It was a tight race, but in the end voters approved a two-year supplemental levy at $647,000 annually in order to continue to meet the community's expectations and provide offerings that exceed the state requirements. As in the past, the District will continue to work toward efficiency while maintaining existing programs and expanding student opportunities yet staying conservative in its spending. Superintendent Higgins and the staff at Kamiah school district thank our community for the voter response in Tuesday’s levy vote. “We appreciate your support and the efforts of the planning committee for sharing the message with our patrons.”

Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force Presentation

When: March 11th
Where: KHS Gym
Time: 5:30pm

Presentation Description:
Learn about the dangers that face teens every day. In doing so, we’ll discuss how computers, cell phones, IPads, digital cameras, gaming systems, social networking applications, and internet blogs all play a role in placing students and families at risk. This presentation is specifically geared towards parents, educators and community leaders who are looking to better understand the technology available to teens today and the way in which child predators use it to exploit them.

This week our Physical Science students completed The Mars Rover Insulation Challenge! Students had the opportunity to design, build, and test their rovers to meet the following design criteria: rovers had to be able to drive in a loop around the classroom using a Sphero Mini robot (donated by the Kamiah Education Foundation), have insulation that would keep water as hot as possible for 10 minutes, and carry 10 rock samples (pennies).

The winning teams were:
1st Period - Brady Cox, Ryan Sackett, and MaKinna Wilson with “Bubbles”
3rd Period - Keegan Robeson, Logan Landmark, and William Millage with “The Glue Ship”

#sciencerules #themarsgeneration

post_text:
KES and Kamiah Jr/Sr High School Clothes Closets

For years now both schools have maintained a “gently used” clothes closet for students in need. This year, sadly our closets are seriously depleted and we could use your support.
With the cold temperatures we are in need of coats and warm hoodies (any size) to add to our closets. Several U of I sorority chapters are donating hats and gloves for Kamiah students and we should be receiving them before the Christmas break.
Other needed items (in all sizes and for both boys and girls):
• Gently used sneakers
• Pants and Shirts
• Packs of socks in all sizes

As always we appreciate your continued support for our schools.
If you have questions please call Terry Law, Family Support Liaison at 208-935-4067.
text:
KES and Kamiah Jr/Sr High School Clothes Closets

For years now both schools have maintained a “gently used” clothes closet for students in need. This year, sadly our closets are seriously depleted and we could use your support.
With the cold temperatures we are in need of coats and warm hoodies (any size) to add to our closets. Several U of I sorority chapters are donating hats and gloves for Kamiah students and we should be receiving them before the Christmas break.
Other needed items (in all sizes and for both boys and girls):
• Gently used sneakers
• Pants and Shirts
• Packs of socks in all sizes

As always we appreciate your continued support for our schools.
If you have questions please call Terry Law, Family Support Liaison at 208-935-4067.

Today's order of Events for HoCo 2019!

Thursday:

Students will report to 5th hour for attendance and then be released for the assembly (around 12:45pm)

games and class competitions

The Hog Roast is from 5pm-7pm in the Multipurpose room
admission is $12 for 18 and over and $9 for 17 and younger at the door

if bought before Friday its $10 for 18 and over and $7 for 17 and younger

#GoKubs!

Kamiah Middle School
September 24, 2019 at 8:28 PM ·

‼️Parents &Guardians‼️

We are now incorporating the use of the Daily Bulletin Via PowerSchool! 😁👍

How to Access📲

1st step:
You will need to have access to your parent portal to PowerSchool: (if you do not have your own parent account, please contact Mrs. Jacobs at the Jr/Sr High School and she will help you get that)

2nd Step:
• Login to powerschool via your parent login info.
• Along the left hand side select Email notification
• Select the box to receive school announcements
• Toward the bottom you can select how often you would like to be notified.

If you have any questions you can contact Mrs. Jacobs at the Jr /Sr High School office and she will be able help answer any questions you have.
